  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4800].
  {panel}

Currently JIRA's encoding (file.encoding system property) is set globally. This means that no matter what language a user picks in their profile preferences, that translation will be served in the default encoding, which may not be able to represent the chosen language.

We need to either store encoding along with locale in the user's preference, or else move to UTF-8 everywhere (there must be _some_ point to unicode).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4794].
  {panel}

Some types of issues (eg "Support Requests") should be private by default.  For this, we need to set the default security level by issue type.

Originally developed in the UK, ITIL defines a set of best practices for IT service management, including Service Support. My company is implementing ITIL service support processes and my impression is that ITIL is becoming quite popular in the IT industry. We have looked at a couple of "ITIL tools", Infra and Remedy, and they have an impressive feature list but are priced way out of our range. We like JIRA and the price is right but it doesn't quite fit with ITIL. We believe we can customize JIRA to fit reasonably well but it would be nice if Atlassian took a look at ITIL and made a few changes to improve the support "out of the box". As we go through our customization of JIRA, I hope to be able to log more specific change requests.

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of 08/07/2010|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
Thanks to all for your continued comments on this issue. However at this time we are not planning to implement ITIL support into JIRA. Please feel free to keep commenting on this issue as we are watching it.
{panel}

